-- Purdue, North Carolina State Win High-Scoring College Football Bowl Games
-- B y   R o b   G l o s t e r
-- 2011-12-28T05:01:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-28/purdue-north-carolina-state-win-high-scoring-college-football-bowl-games.html
Reggie Pegram had two touchdowns and
Raheem Mostert ran a kickoff back 99 yards for another score as
 Purdue University  defeated Western Michigan University 37-32 in
college football’s Little Caesars Bowl at Detroit’s Ford Field.  Both teams finished the season with 7-6 records.  In the Belk Bowl at Bank of America Stadium in Charlotte,
North Carolina, Mike Glennon threw three touchdown passes as
North Carolina State (8-5) won 31-24 against Louisville (7-6).  T.J. Graham had touchdown receptions of 67 and six yards
for the Wolfpack.  To contact the reporter on this story:
